('91048a11-3bd4-5875-bca1-7100c570b4a9', '20d6333f-d9da-4330-b0cf-8ed640c01ec4', 'He wrote a letter ___ his friend.', '他給他的朋友寫了一封信。', 'to', 'from', 'with', 'for', '表示動作的「對象」。', 'write to → 寫給某人'),
('e82fc05e-a981-56a9-8600-3b0b62d8709d', '05737cfc-81a1-42b1-9d5d-0c18e7a4370a', 'Despite the heavy rain, the protesters decided to carry ___ with their march.', '儘管大雨滂沱，示威者仍決定繼續他們的遊行。', 'on', 'out', 'away', 'back', '副詞，與 carry 連用表示「繼續」。', 'carry (攜帶) + on (繼續) → 繼續做某事。'),
('69ffa608-df80-5a07-9055-e05ff923193d', '0b994cbb-35f3-4ef0-a95a-70ecd51e8a90', 'He is ___ a teacher; he is a student.', '他不是一名老師；他是一名學生。', 'not', 'always', 'still', 'really', '表示「不」的否定副詞。', '看到 not 就想到 no，代表「不」的意思。');
